<subSubSection id="24CB1080FF95FFCBFAB2AD0881ADFD2C" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFF95FFCBFAB2AD0881ADFD2C" blockId="33.[151,1437,505,713]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF95FFCBFAB2AD08815EFD64" bold="true" box="[199,315,614,640]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded in 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FF95FFCBF976AD0883C9FD64" box="[771,940,614,640]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">São Paulo state</collectingRegion>
as 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FF95FFCBF9A4AD088419FD64" box="[977,1148,614,640]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Aegeon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boschii">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF95FFCBF9A4AD088419FD64" box="[977,1148,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Aegeon boschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Christoffersen (1988), but the exact locality was not mentioned. According to Christoffersen (1988) the specimens were collected at 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFF95FFCBFF28ADE485F2FD40" box="[1373,1431,650,676]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="m" value="60.0">60 m</quantity>
, in sand and mud, 15.56 °C.
</paragraph>
